## Documentation update cascade

When making structural changes, update the relevant docs to prevent staleness. The rule: if you change the reality, update anything that describes that reality.

| If you... | Update these |
|-----------|-------------|
| Add or remove a site | `README.md` site table, `project-context.mdc` section 1, CI workflow matrices |
| Change a domain or brand name | `README.md`, `niche.config.json`, `project-context.mdc` section 1 |
| Add or remove a page route | `project-context.mdc` section 1 (Unique pages), sitemap.ts |
| Add or remove a blog category | `project-context.mdc` section 6, create/remove hub page, update middleware |
| Change URL structure or slugify logic | `project-context.mdc` sections 5a/5b, middleware.ts |
| Fix or find an issue | `Admin/ISSUE_LOG.md` (see protocol above) |
| Change CI workflows or automation | `project-context.mdc` section 18 (Operational Controls) |
| Change the config system or architecture | `project-context.mdc` (relevant section) |

Do NOT update docs for routine content changes (new blog posts, topic generation, analytics runs). These are high-frequency and the docs deliberately exclude volatile counts.

Run `python scripts/validate_docs.py` after structural changes to verify consistency.

