## Editorial Optimization Pipeline

Before running `scripts/optimize_content_editorial.py`, read `Admin/EDITORIAL_PIPELINE_LESSONS.md` for known failure modes and the guardrail checklist.

**Required workflow:**
1. Run with `--dry-run` to preview which posts will be analyzed
2. Run the analysis (generates `scripts/editorial_review.json`)
3. Run with `--validate-only` to check all proposals against current content
4. Review warnings (prices, tax years, duplicate headings)
5. Run with `--apply` to apply changes
6. Run `python scripts/validate_blog_content.py` to verify no content was corrupted
7. Run `npm run build` from the site's `web/` directory to confirm build passes

If you encounter a new failure mode, add it to `Admin/EDITORIAL_PIPELINE_LESSONS.md` with the next sequential ID.
